<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Cartridge Pinout Orientation [SOLVED]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6195&amp;p=58646#p58646"><![CDATA[
If you have an actual cart just open the case and look at the PCB: the pins are numbered. Or look for high-resolution scans of PCBs on Google, the numbers should be quite visible.<br /><br />If you are facing the label of the cart, I think pin 1 is the rightmost one of the side that's facing you, and the count increases to the left, up until pin 36. Behind pin 1 is pin 37, and the count goes until pin 72 on the left.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Mar 19, 2010 3:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
