<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Cartridge Pinout Orientation [SOLVED]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6195&amp;p=58645#p58645"><![CDATA[
Hey guys,<br /><br />I'm trying to work up a quick prototyping cart board for my emulator.  I've got a cartridge-related question.  I've found plenty of docs that tell you what the pin definitions and pin numbering is for the original NES cartridge, but I can't find one that gives you the exact orientation of the pinout diagram relative to a physical cart (i.e. if you were holding it in your hand).<br /><br />For example, if I'm holding a cart, with the game label facing me and the connector-side down, which pin is pin 1?<br /><br />1) Front pin, left-side<br />2) Back pin, left-side<br />3) Front pin, right-side<br />4) Back pin, right-side<br /><br />And from the pinouts that I have seen, pin 2 is _adjacent_ to pin 1 and not behind pin 1 (i.e. on the other side of the board).  I want to make sure I get this pinout 100% correct because I don't want to have to re-spin the board because I made a dumb mistake.<br /><br />THANKS! <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />Jonathon<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3962">jwdonal</a> — Fri Mar 19, 2010 2:32 pm</p><hr />
